<subSubSection id="4FFC65060B61165378E8F82424ACFF75" lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="123" pageId="17" pageNumber="122" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="0759368D0B61165378E8F82424ACFF75" blockId="17.[136,1451,2022,2084]" lastBlockId="18.[136,1452,158,617]" lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="123" pageId="17" pageNumber="122">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B61165078E8F82426D7F7A9" bold="true" box="[189,397,2022,2048]" pageId="17" pageNumber="122">Taxonomic notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B61165079FFF8242565F7A9" authorityName="R. E. Fries" authorityYear="1908" box="[426,575,2022,2048]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="17" pageNumber="122" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="regnellii">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B61165079FFF8242565F7A9" box="[426,575,2022,2048]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="122">Sida regnellii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to section 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B6116507B45F82424CAF7A9" authorityName="Fryxell" authorityYear="1985" baseAuthorityName="de Candolle" box="[784,912,2022,2048]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Cordifoliae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="17" pageNumber="122" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B6116507B45F82424CAF7A9" box="[784,912,2022,2048]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="122">Cordifoliae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the indument densely stellate-tomentose; leaf blades lanceolate to ovate, dentate-crenate throughout, basally more or less cordate, features pointed out by 
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B6116537D0FF7C82789FF10" author="Fryxell, P. A." lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="123" pageId="17" pageNumber="122" pagination="62 - 91" refId="ref18743" refString="Fryxell, P. A. (1985) The North and Central American species of Sida. Sida, Contributions to Botany 11: 62 - 91." type="journal article" year="1985">Fryxell (1985)</bibRefCitation>
for this section (
<tableCitation id="4A6403360B62165379DEFF5C2684FF11" box="[395,478,158,184]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="2.[136,224,340,364]" captionTargetBox="[144,1440,425,1289]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="TABLE 1. Sections of Sida with species occurring in Rio Grande do Sul state, and their diagnostic features, according to Fryxell (1985) and Krapovickas (2003)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/539966050B72164378DDFE962568FE39" pageId="18" pageNumber="123" tableUuid="539966050B72164378DDFE962568FE39">Table 1</tableCitation>
). It can be distinguished from similar species by its muticous or submuticous mericarps (with aristae up to 
<quantity id="C01E9B680B621653790FFF0026EAFF74" box="[346,432,194,221]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="18" pageNumber="123" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
long) and by the pink corolla (
<figureCitation id="9FDD2A080B6216537B5CFF0024F0FF75" box="[777,938,194,220]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="19.[136,229,1920,1942]" captionTargetBox="[190,1398,190,1896]" captionTargetId="figure-17@19.[190,1398,190,1896]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 9. A–E. Sida regnellii. A. Flower. B. Adaxial surface of leaf. C. Branch with flower, leaves and mature schizocarp. D. Habit. E. Branch with leaves and mature schizocarps. F–J. Sida rhombifolia. F, G. Flowers. H. Abaxial surface of leaf. I. Adaxial surface of leaf. J. Branch with mature mericarps. L–P. Sida riedelii. L. Flower. M. Branch with leaves, flower bud and mature mericarp. N.Adaxial surface of leaf. O. Abaxial surface of leaf. P. Branch with tubercle at petiole base. Photographs by Martin Grings and Sérgio A.L. Bordignon (D)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415507" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415507/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="123">Figures 9A–E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="9FDD2A080B6216537BE3FF0024B3FF75" box="[950,1001,194,220]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="26.[136,229,1957,1979]" captionTargetBox="[196,1391,245,1933]" captionTargetId="figure-54@26.[196,1391,245,1933]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 14. Mericarps. A. Sida anomala. B. Sida confusa. C. Sida farroupilhensis. D. Sida glaziovii. E. Sida cerradoensis. F. Sida cordifolia. G. Sida dubia. H. Sida linifolia. I. Sida lonchitis. J. Sida nemorensis. K. Sida paradoxa. L. Sida planicaulis. M. Sida potentilloides.N. Sida reitzii. O. Sida regnellii. P. Sida rhombifolia.Q. Sida riedelii. R. Sida rubifolia.S. Sida spinosa.T. Sida tuberculata. U. Sida urens. V. Sida viarum. Photographs by Martin Grings." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415519" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415519/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="123">14O</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4FFC65060B62165378E8FF242415FE71" pageId="18" pageNumber="123" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="0759368D0B62165378E8FF242415FE71" blockId="18.[136,1452,158,617]" pageId="18" pageNumber="123">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B62165378E8FF242583FEA9" bold="true" box="[189,729,230,256]" pageId="18" pageNumber="123">Distribution, habitat and conservation status:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B6216537AA0FF2424D0FEA9" authorityName="R. E. Fries" authorityYear="1908" box="[757,906,230,256]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="18" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="regnellii">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B6216537AA0FF2424D0FEA9" box="[757,906,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="123">Sida regnellii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in 
<collectingCountry id="7FF1761D0B6216537BACFF242331FEA9" box="[1017,1131,230,256]" name="Argentina" pageId="18" pageNumber="123">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="7FF1761D0B6216537C20FF252387FEA8" box="[1141,1245,231,257]" name="Paraguay" pageId="18" pageNumber="123">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="7FF1761D0B6216537D47FF24220CFEA9" box="[1298,1366,230,256]" name="Brazil" pageId="18" pageNumber="123">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="C522F86F0B6216537D31FF24278EFE8D" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="18" pageNumber="123">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="C522F86F0B62165378B4FEC82677FE8D" box="[225,301,266,292]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="18" pageNumber="123">Paraná</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="C522F86F0B6216537933FEC82566FE8D" box="[358,572,266,292]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="18" pageNumber="123">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
states) (
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B6216537AC9FEC82425FE8D" author="Zuloaga, F. O. &amp; Morrone, O. &amp; Belgrano M. J." box="[668,895,266,292]" pageId="18" pageNumber="123" pagination="1 - 3348" refId="ref20813" refString="Zuloaga, F. O., Morrone, O. &amp; Belgrano M. J. (2008) Catalogo de las plantas vasculares del Cono Sur (Argentina, sur de Brasil, Chile, Paraguay y Uruguay). Monographs in Systematic Botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden 107: 1 - 3348." type="journal article" year="2008">
Zuloaga 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B6216537B57FEC92466FE8D" box="[770,828,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="123">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B6216537BD9FEC82344FE8D" author="Bovini, M. G." box="[908,1054,266,292]" pageId="18" pageNumber="123" refId="ref18092" refString="Bovini, M. G. (2020) Sida in Lista de Especies da Flora do Brasil. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / jabot / floradobrasil / FB 9206 (accessed 7 July 2020)" type="url" year="2020">Bovini 2020</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingRegion id="C522F86F0B6216537C04FEC8227DFE8D" box="[1105,1319,266,292]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="18" pageNumber="123">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
the species occurs in Inland sub-montane grassland, Bush grassland, Coastal grassland, 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B6216537BA5FEEC2310FEE1" box="[1008,1098,302,328]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Aristida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="18" pageNumber="114" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Aristida</taxonomicName>
grassland, and in Shallow soil grassland (
<figureCitation id="9FDD2A080B6216537957FE90263FFEC5" box="[258,357,338,364]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="17.[136,229,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[267,1344,252,1880]" captionTargetId="figure-17@17.[205,1383,190,1929]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 8. Distribution map of Sida riedelii, S. ramoniana, S. regnellii, S. reitzii and S. tuberculata in Rio Grande do Sul state, Brazil." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415505/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="123">Figure 8</figureCitation>
). With the available records, the species is here considered Least Concern (LC) with an EOO of 
<quantity id="C01E9B680B62165378DDFEB4261AFE3A" box="[136,320,374,403]" metricMagnitude="8" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.74636157" pageId="18" pageNumber="123" unit="km" value="974636.157">974,636.157 km</quantity>
² and an AOO of 
<quantity id="C01E9B680B6216537A56FEB42501FE3A" box="[515,603,374,403]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.04" pageId="18" pageNumber="123" unit="km" value="304.0">304 km</quantity>
². Although it can be considered EN by the AOO, conditions B(a), B(b) and B(c) were not met. In addition, the species is common in its area of occurrence, mainly in the state of 
<collectingRegion id="C522F86F0B6216537D50FE5827EAFE71" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="18" pageNumber="123">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
, which is not reflected in the number of records in herbaria.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
